This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their proper channel scaling for model reduction. It also involves image classification tasks such as ImageNet and CIFAR-10. 

It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm for model reduction that is based on measuring information redundancy and effective flops. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with optimizing CNN models for better performance and efficiency. 

Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is also a likely sub-category as the paper involves optimizing neural networks, which is a common topic in this field. 

Finally, Multimedia (cs.MM) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves image classification tasks and reducing the size of CNN models, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
